This paper deals with optimization problems and proposes a framework based on CP-nets and soft constraints to handle hard and soft constraints as well as conditional preferences. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category, which deals with intelligent agents, reasoning, and decision making. Additionally, the paper discusses complexity results and approximation techniques, which are common topics in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a framework for handling multiple types of information, which could be relevant to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency and uniformity of the proposed framework, which could be relevant to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
